    en: "The Social Security Administration issues replacement cards at no cost under 42 USC § 405. A U.S. citizen with a my Social Security online account can request a replacement online for free. Anyone else applies in person at a Social Security office with proof of identity and citizenship or immigration status. There is no fee. The replacement card has the same Social Security number as the original. A person is limited to 3 replacement cards per year and 10 in a lifetime, with exceptions for name changes, immigration status changes, and certain hardship situations."
